==English==
===Etymology===
From Greek ''satyr'', a mythological creature, as in a [[satyr play]].

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''satire'''
# A [[literary]] [[technique]] of [[writing]] or [[art]] which principally [[ridicule|ridicules]] its [[subject]] often as an intended means of [[provoke|provoking]] or [[preventing]] [[change]], which usually incorporates criticism.

